rce":["from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\n","\n","# Encode labels\n","df['label'] = df['label'].map({'ham':0, 'spam':1})\n","\n","# TF-IDF\n","vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=3000)\n","X = vectorizer.fit_transform(df['email']).toarray()\n","y = df['label'].values"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"14abe08b","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.00382,"end_time":"2026-05-27T16:43:04.9154+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-05-27T16:43:04.91158+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["## TF-IDF Vectorizer\n","\n","The **TF-IDF Vectorizer** in scikit-learn converts text into numerical features so machine learning models can understand it.\n","\n","TF-IDF stands for:\n","\n","* **TF (Term Frequency)** → how often a word appears in a document\n","* **IDF (Inverse Document Frequency)** → how rare the word is across all documents\n","\n","### Intuition\n","\n","* Common words like *“the”, “is”* → low importance\n","* Rare but meaningful words → high importance\n","\n","### Formula\n","\n","**TF-IDF = TF × IDF**\n","\n","Where:\n","\n","* TF = (word count in document / total words in document)\n","* IDF = log(total documents / number of documents containing the word)\n","\n","### Example Dataset\n","\n","```python\n","corpus = [\n","    \"I love machine learning\",\n","    \"Machine learning is fun\",\n","    \"I love coding\"\n","]\n","```\n","\n","#### Vocabulary Creation\n","\n","The vectorizer first builds a vocabulary.\n","\n","After preprocessing (lowercasing, tokenizing), unique words are:\n","\n","```python\n","['coding', 'fun', 'is', 'learning', 'love', 'machine']\n","```\n","\n","Notice:\n","\n","* `\"I\"` is removed because single-letter tokens are ignored by default.\n","* Words are sorted alphabetically.\n","\n","#### Term Frequency (TF)\n","\n","TF measures how often a word appears in a document.\n","\n","$$\n","TF(t,d) = \\frac{\\text{count of term t in document d}}{\\text{total terms in d}}\n","$$\n","\n","Example for Document 1: `I love machine learning` => Words: `love, machine, learning`\n","\n","Each appears once.\n","\n","So TF values:\n","\n","| Word     | TF  |\n","| -------- | --- |\n","| love     | 1/3 |\n","| machine  | 1/3 |\n","| learning | 1/3 |\n","\n","#### Inverse Document Frequency (IDF)\n","\n","IDF reduces importance of common words.\n","\n","$$\n","IDF(t) = \\log\\left(\\frac{1+n}{1+df(t)}\\right) + 1\n","$$\n","\n","Where:\n","\n","* $n$ = total documents\n","* $df(t)$ = number of documents containing term $t$\n","\n","We have: Total documents = 3\n","\n","#### Document Frequencies\n","\n","| Word     | Appears In | df |\n","| -------- | ---------- | -- |\n","| coding   | Doc3       | 1  |\n","| fun      | Doc2       | 1  |\n","| is       | Doc2       | 1  |\n","| learning | Doc1, Doc2 | 2  |\n","| love     | Doc1, Doc3 | 2  |\n","| machine  | Doc1, Doc2 | 2  |\n","\n","#### IDF Calculations\n","\n","**For words appearing once:**\n","\n","Example: `\"coding\"`\n","\n","$$\n","IDF = \\log\\left(\\frac{1+3}{1+1}\\right)+1\n","$$\n","\n","$$\n","= \\log(2)+1\n","$$\n","\n","$$\n","= 0.693 + 1\n","$$\n","\n","$$\n","= 1.693\n","$$\n","\n","So:\n","\n","```text\n","coding, fun, is → 1.693\n","```\n","\n","**For words appearing twice:**\n","\n","Example: `\"machine\"`\n","\n","$$\n","IDF = \\log\\left(\\frac{4}{3}\\right)+1\n","$$\n","\n","$$\n","= 0.288 + 1\n","$$\n","\n","$$\n","= 1.288\n","$$\n","\n","So:\n","\n","```text\n","machine, learning, love → 1.288\n","```\n","\n","#### TF-IDF Calculation\n","\n","$$\n","TFIDF = TF \\times IDF\n","$$\n","\n","**Document 1**: `I love machine learning` TF: `1/3 = 0.333`\n","\n","Scores\n","\n","| Word     | TF    | IDF   | TF-IDF |\n","| -------- | ----- | ----- | ------ |\n","| love     | 0.333 | 1.288 | 0.429  |\n","| machine  | 0.333 | 1.288 | 0.429  |\n","| learning | 0.333 | 1.288 | 0.429  |\n","\n","**Document 2**: `Machine learning is fun` Terms: `machine, learning, is, fun`, TF: `1/4 = 0.25`\n","\n","Scores\n","\n","| Word     | TF-IDF               |\n","| -------- | -------------------- |\n","| machine  | 0.25 × 1.288 = 0.322 |\n","| learning | 0.322                |\n","| is       | 0.25 × 1.693 = 0.423 |\n","| fun      | 0.423                |\n","\n","**Document 3**: `I love coding`, Terms: `love, coding`, TF: `1/2 = 0.5`\n","\n","Scores\n","\n","| Word   | TF-IDF              |\n","| ------ | ------------------- |\n","| love   | 0.5 × 1.288 = 0.644 |\n","| coding | 0.5 × 1.693 = 0.846 |\n","\n","#### Normalization\n","\n","Scikit-learn normalizes vectors using **[L2 normalization](https://medium.com/@reina07/16-data-normalization-methods-using-python-with-examples-part-5-of-6-8744cb2b2e15)**.\n","\n","$$\n","\\text{Normalized Vector} =\n","\\frac{v}{||v||}\n","$$\n","\n","This scales vectors so their length becomes 1.\n","\n","That’s why actual output values differ slightly from raw TF-IDF calculations.\n","\n","#### Final Matrix Output\n","\n","Approximate output:\n","\n","```python\n","Feature Names:\n","['coding' 'fun' 'is' 'learning' 'love' 'machine']\n","```\n","\n","TF-IDF Matrix:\n","\n","```python\n","[\n"," [0.000, 0.000, 0.000, 0.577, 0.577, 0.577],\n"," [0.000, 0.623, 0.623, 0.474, 0.000, 0.474],\n"," [0.796, 0.000, 0.000, 0.000, 0.605, 0.000]\n","]\n","```\n","\n","#### Matrix Interpretation\n","\n","Row 1\n","\n","```text\n","\"I love machine learning\"\n","[0,0,0,0.577,0.577,0.577]\n","```\n","\n","* learning → important\n","* love → important\n","* machine → important\n","\n","Row 2\n","\n","```text\n","\"Machine learning is fun\"\n","```\n","\n","Higher scores for: fun, is, because they appear in only one document.\n","\n","Row 3\n","\n","```text\n","\"I love coding\"\n","```\n","\n","Highest score: coding, because it is rare across documents.\n","\n","### Important Parameters\n","\n","* `max_features` → limit number of words\n","* `stop_words='english'` → remove common words\n","* `ngram_range=(1,2)` → include bigrams\n","* `min_df` / `max_df` → filter rare/common words\n","\n","### When to Use TF-IDF\n","\n","* Text classification (spam detection, sentiment analysis)\n","* Document similarity\n","* Search engines / information retrieval\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":5,"id":"8f07d5d5","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-27T16:43:04.9248Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-27T16:43:04.923753Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-27T16:43:04.94841Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-27T16:43:04.947494Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.031362,"end_time":"2026-05-27T16:43:04.950346+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-05-27T16:43:04.918984+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"data":{"text/html":["<div>\n","<style scoped>\n","    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n","        vertical-align: middle;\n","    }\n","\n","    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n","        vertical-align: top;\n","    }\n","\n","    .dataframe thead th {\n","        text-align: right;\n","    }\n","</style>\n","<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n","  <thead>\n","    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n","      <th></th>\n","      <th>00</th>\n","      <th>000</th>\n","      <th>008704050406</th>\n","      <th>01223585334</th>\n","      <th>02</th>\n","      <th>0207</th>\n","      <th>02073162414</th>\n","      <th>021</th>\n","      <th>03</th>\n","      <th>04</th>\n","      <th>...</th>\n","      <th>yourself</th>\n","      <th>yr</th>\n","      <th>yrs</th>\n","      <th>yummy</th>\n","      <th>yun</th>\n","      <th>yunny</th>\n","      <th>yuo</th>\n","      <th>yup</th>\n","      <th>zed</th>\n","      <th>zindgi</th>\n","    </tr>\n","  </thead>\n","  <tbody>\n","    <tr>\n","      <th>0</th>\n","      <td>0.0</td>\n","      <td>0.0</td>\n","      <td>0.0</td>\n","      <td>0.0</td>\n","      <td>0.0</td>\n","      <td>0.0</td>\n","      <td>0.0</td>\n","      <td>0.0</td>\n","      <td>0.0</td>\n","      <td>0.0</td>\n","      <td>...</td>\n","      <td>0.0</td>\n","      <td>0.0</td